values.label: Consolidated weight

values.label: Net weight
values.comment: [6160] Weight of goods including any packaging that normally going with the goods.

values.label: Goods item gross weight
values.comment: [6292] Weight (mass) of goods including packing but excluding the carrier's equipment.

values.label: Total net weight
values.comment: Total weight of goods excluding packaging.

values.label: Consignment gross weight
values.comment: [6012] Total gross weight (mass) of all goods items referred to as one consignment including packaging but excluding any transport equipment.

values.label: Net net weight
values.comment: [6048] Weight (mass) if goods without any packaging.

values.label: Stern thrust
values.comment: Force exerted by a thruster installed at the stern of a vessel.

values.label: Bow thrust
values.comment: Force exerted by a thruster installed at the bow of a vessel.

values.label: Hydrate content of an alcoholic product at bottling
values.comment: The hydrate content of an alcoholic product at the moment of bottling.

values.label: Number of units per pallet
values.comment: The number of units contained on a pallet.

values.label: Fat content
values.comment: An indication of the fat content of a product.

values.label: Transport means gross weight
values.comment: [6300] The measure of the overall size of a ship determined in accordance with the provisions of the International Convention on Tonnage Measurement of Ships, 1969.

values.label: Net tonnage of the vessel
values.comment: [6302] The measure of the useful capacity of a ship determined in accordance with the provisions of the International Convention on Tonnage Measurement of Ships, 1969.

values.label: Humidity
values.comment: Degree of moisture.

values.label: Voltage
values.comment: Electromotive force, or difference of electronic potential between two points.

values.label: Power consumption
values.comment: Value of energy consumption.

values.label: Heat dissipation
values.comment: Measurement of the rate of dispersal of heat.

values.label: Air flow
values.comment: Measurement of the flow of air.

values.label: Shock impact
values.comment: Measurement of the impact of a shock.

values.label: Operative temperature
values.comment: Temperature identified system or process works according to specifications.

values.label: Non operative temperature
values.comment: Temperature identified system or process does not work according to specifications.

values.label: Gross volume
values.comment: The volume unadjusted for factors such as temperature or gravity.

values.label: Net volume
values.comment: The volume after adjustment for factors such as temperature or gravity.

values.label: Water content
values.comment: Water content in product.

values.label: Tensile stress
values.comment: The measured tensile stress.

values.label: Fibrosity
values.comment: The measured fibrosity.

values.label: Gauge length
values.comment: The measured gauge length.

values.label: Radius
values.comment: The measured radius.

values.label: Straightness
values.comment: Straightness of the item.

values.label: Strain
values.comment: The measured strain.

values.label: Item length when unrolled
values.comment: The length of an item when unrolled.

values.label: Item area when unrolled
values.comment: The area occupied by an item when unrolled.

values.label: Original wort
values.comment: Measure of the malt and hops content of beer, before fermentation has taken place.

values.label: Volume
values.comment: The amount of air space taken up by the entity identified in the 6311 qualifier.

values.label: Angle
values.comment: The angle of an object.

values.label: Peg hole horizontal distance from package leftmost edge
values.comment: Horizontal distance from the left most edge of the package to the center of the hole into which the peg is inserted.

values.label: Peg hole vertical distance from package top
values.comment: Vertical distance from the top of the package to the top of the hole into which the peg is inserted.

values.label: Number of layers per pallet

values.label: Product strengh, chemical
values.comment: The amount of the single active chemical ingredient within a product.

values.label: Product strength basis, chemical
values.comment: Amount of product used as the basis for the specification of the chemical product strenght.

values.label: Item weight
values.comment: Weight at line item level.

values.label: Payload weight, maximum
values.comment: The maximum weight of a payload.

values.label: Weight of conveyance
values.comment: Tonnage of conveyance.

values.label: Conveyance summer dead weight
values.comment: Registered summer dead weight total tonnage of the vessel.

values.label: Containerized cargo on vessel's weight
values.comment: Total weight of containerized cargo on vessel.

values.label: Non-containerized cargo on vessel's weight
values.comment: Total weight of non-containerized cargo on vessel.

values.label: Ascertained weight
values.comment: [4240] Endorsement of the true weight (mass) as ascertained or verified.

values.label: Chargeable weight
values.comment: The weight on which charges are based.

values.label: Estimated gross weight
values.comment: Estimated weight (mass) of goods, including packing and excluding carrier's.

values.label: Estimated volume
values.comment: Estimated size or measure of anything in three dimensions.

values.label: Vessel overall length
values.comment: Total overall length of the vessel.

values.label: Loading meters
values.comment: [6046] (6042) (6044) The length in a vehicle, whereby the complete width and height over that length is needed for the goods.

values.label: Number of axles
values.comment: Number of axles of movable equipment or means of transport on wheels.

values.label: Payload
values.comment: The revenue-producing load carried by a means of transport.

values.label: Start position in the length
values.comment: The starting position from the beginning of an item located in the length direction.

values.label: End position in the length
values.comment: The end position from the beginning of an item located in the length direction.

values.label: Start position in the width
values.comment: The start position from the beginning of an item located in the width direction.

values.label: End position in the width
values.comment: The end position from the beginning of an item located in the width direction.

values.label: Start position in the thickness
values.comment: The start position from the beginning of an item located in the thickness direction.

values.label: End position in the thickness
values.comment: The end position from the beginning of an item located in the thickness direction.

values.label: Transport container actual filling weight
values.comment: Actual filling weight of a transport container.

values.label: Transport container maximum capacity
values.comment: Maximum capacity of a transport container.

values.label: Declared net weight
values.comment: The declared net weight of a product or products used for invoicing, customs or transport purposes.

values.label: Loading height
values.comment: Maximum height of products or packages loaded onto a given transportation device or equipment such as a pallet.

values.label: Stacking height
values.comment: Maximum height up to which the same product or package may be placed one upon the other for storage purposes.

values.label: Calculated weight
values.comment: The calculated weight of the item based on the ordered dimensions.

values.label: Ferrite
values.comment: The chemical composition ferrite.

values.label: Impurity
values.comment: The impurity of the product i.e. the measurement of other chemical elements not normally appearing in a product.

values.label: Grain size
values.comment: The grain size.

values.label: Lanthanides
values.comment: The chemical element Lanthanides.

values.label: Elasticity
values.comment: The value of the elasticity.

values.label: Drained weight
values.comment: The weight of a product when all liquids used in the packaging of the product have been removed.

values.label: Gallium
values.comment: Measurement of the gallium component.

values.label: Strontium
values.comment: Measurement of the strontium component.

values.label: Area
values.comment: Extent or measure of a surface.

values.label: Equipment storage limitation
values.comment: Maximum storage limit of the equipment.

values.label: Radioactive index of transport
values.comment: The index of transport determines the maximum radiation level at a distance of 1m from the external surface.

values.label: Radioactivity
values.comment: Activity of radioactive material.

values.label: Average gross weight
values.comment: Weight which is the outcome of the division of the total gross weight by the number of units.

values.label: Forward draft
values.comment: Depth of water from the surface of water to the bottom of the vessel measured at the draft mark of the bow.

values.label: After draft
values.comment: Depth of water from the surface of water to the bottom of the vessel measured at the draft mark of the stern.

values.label: Acidity
values.comment: The quality, state, or degree of being acid.

values.label: Transport equipment gross weight
values.comment: [6294] Weight of a transport equipment including the cargo and carrier's equipment.

values.label: Total transport equipment gross weight
values.comment: Total weight of all transport equipment including the cargo and carrier's equipment.

values.label: Acidity of juice
values.comment: Acid measurement of juice.

values.label: Penetrometry
values.comment: Measurement of force required to drive a standard penetrating stamp.

values.label: Durofel
values.comment: Measurement of the elastic force using a standard penetrating stamp.

values.label: Juice weight per 100 grams
values.comment: Measurement of weight of juice, based on 100 grams of the entire weight.

values.label: Fruit skin colour
values.comment: Measurement of the colouring of the epidermis of a fruit.

values.label: Angle of bend
values.comment: The measured angle of bend.

values.label: Fixed incremental measurement
values.comment: The measurement of the fixed increment.

values.label: Durofel D10
values.comment: Measure of the elastic force of the pulp of a fruit. It is measured with a penetrating stamp with diameter 10.

values.label: Durofel D25
values.comment: Measure of the elastic force of the pulp of a fruit. It is measured with a penetrating stamp with diameter 25.

values.label: Durofel D50
values.comment: Measure of the elastic force of the pulp of a fruit. It is measured with a penetrating stamp with diameter 50.

values.label: Maximum stacking weight
values.comment: The maximum weight which may be stacked upon a product or package without the product or packaging being crushed.

values.label: Gross measure cube
values.comment: The total cubic space occupied by an item, taking into account any protruding components, arrived at by multiplying the maximum length, width and height.

values.label: Percentage fat content in dry matter
values.comment: The percentage of fat content in dry matter.

values.label: Saccharometric content
values.comment: Measurement of the sugar content of a solution.

values.label: Hydrate content of an alcoholic product after bottling
values.comment: The hydrate content which occurs in an alcoholic product after bottling.

values.label: Anhydrous content
values.comment: The non-water content.

values.label: Certified weight
values.comment: Weight which has been certified.

values.label: Freeboard
values.comment: The vertical distance between the waterline and the upper edge of the deck line.

values.label: Maximum vessel draught
values.comment: The depth of water needed to float the ship (Maximum vessel draught according to Load Line Certificate IMO, MSC/Circ. 920 15 June 1999).

values.label: Net explosive weight
values.comment: Mass of the explosive part or substance of goods without any packing.

values.label: Radioactive criticality safety index
values.comment: A number, assigned to fissile material i.e. material capable of sustaining a nuclear chain reaction, which is used to provide control over the accumulation of packages containing such material.

values.label: Waste currently on board
values.comment: Amount of waste on board at the moment of the notification.

values.label: Waste to be delivered at waste reception facility
values.comment: Amount of waste to be delivered to a waste reception facility, e.g. in the port of call.

values.label: Waste to be generated until next port of call, estimated
values.comment: Estimated amount of waste to be generated between creation of the current notification and arrival in the next port of call, irrespective of use of incinerator or compactor or disposal at sea.

values.label: Waste remaining on board at departure
values.comment: Amount of waste remaining on board when leaving the port of call.

values.label: Colour depth
values.comment: The number of distinct colours represented, e.g. in an image or in a display.

values.label: Colour depth, maximum
values.comment: The maximum number of distinct colours that can be represented, e.g. in an image or in a display.

values.label: Image resolution
values.comment: The level of detail of an image.

values.label: Device resolution, maximum
values.comment: The maximum level of detail produced by a device.

values.label: Acoustic absorption coefficient
values.comment: The portion of sound energy a surface absorbs, measured at different frequencies.

values.label: Billed weight
values.comment: The measured billed weight.

values.label: Breaking load
values.comment: The measured breaking load.

values.label: Platinum
values.comment: The measurement of the platinum component.

values.label: Silver
values.comment: The measurement of the silver component.

values.label: List
values.comment: The leaning or inclination of a vessel expressed in degrees port or starboard.

values.label: Trim
values.comment: The condition of a vessel with reference to its longitudinal axis.

values.label: Free water
values.comment: The volume of water present in a container that is not in suspension in the contained liquid.

values.label: Bands
values.comment: The measured bands.

values.label: API (American Petroleum Institute) gravity
values.comment: The relative density of petroleum liquids as specified by a standard developed by the API.

values.label: Petroleum gross observed volume
values.comment: The total volume of all petroleum liquids and sediment and water, excluding free water, at observed temperature and pressure.

values.label: Petroleum gross standard volume
values.comment: The total volume of all petroleum liquids, sediment, and water excluding free water, corrected by the appropriate volume correction factor for the observed temperature and American Petroleum Institute relative density, or density to a standard temperature.

values.label: Volume variance
values.comment: The change in the volume measurement.

values.label: Petroleum net standard volume
values.comment: The total volume of all petroleum liquids, excluding sediment and water and free water, corrected by the appropriate volume correction factor for the observed temperature and American Petroleum Institute gravity relative to density or to a standard temperature.

values.label: Material on-board quantity, after discharge
values.comment: The material in vessel tanks, void spaces, and pipelines after discharge.

values.label: Petroleum total calculated volume
values.comment: The total volume of all petroleum liquids, sediment and water corrected by the appropriate volume correction factor for the observed temperature and American Petroleum Institute (API) gravity, relative density, or density to a standard temperature.

values.label: Petroleum total observed volume
values.comment: The total volume of all petroleum liquids, sediment and water and free water at observed temperature and pressure.

values.label: Innage gauge distance
values.comment: The measured distance from the surface of the liquid to a fixed datum plate or to the tank bottom.

values.label: Petroleum net standard weight
values.comment: The total weight of all petroleum liquids excluding sediments, water and free water.

values.label: Sediment and water in petroleum
values.comment: The measurement of non-hydrocarbon solid material and water in suspension in petroleum liquid.

values.label: Observed reference height, tank
values.comment: The observed distance from the tank bottom or datum plate to the established reference point.

values.label: Reference height, tank
values.comment: The measured distance from the tank bottom or datum plate to the established reference point.

values.label: Ullage gauge distance
values.comment: The measured distance from the cargo liquid surface to the reference point.

values.label: Trim correction
values.comment: The correction applied to the observed gauge or observed volume when a vessel is not on an even keel.

values.label: Bow to bridge distance
values.comment: The distance between the bow and the bridge of a vessel.

values.label: Peg hole number
values.comment: Used to identify the peg hole if more than one hole is present in the product or packaging.

values.label: Number of inner packs
values.comment: Indicates the number of non coded physical groupings (inner packs) of next lower level trade items within the current trade item level.

values.label: Number of next level trade items within inner pack
values.comment: The number of next lower level trade items contained within the physical non-coded grouping (inner pack).

values.label: Number of trade items per pallet layer
values.comment: The number of trade items contained on a single layer of a pallet.

values.label: Packed items layer height
values.comment: The height of a single layer of packed items.

values.label: Packing material weight, skin tight covering
values.comment: The weight measurement of the packing material used for skin tight covering (e.g. when packaging prepared meats, poultry, cheese, and other food products).

values.label: Brightness
values.comment: The measured brightness.

values.label: Brakes
values.comment: The measured brakes.

values.label: Components labelled for recycling percentage
values.comment: Percentage of trade item components that clearly label how to facilitate product disassembly and recycling.

values.label: Renewable plastic components percentage, by net weight
values.comment: The percentage of the plastic components only made from rapidly renewable plant-based material by net weight of product.

values.label: Clamp pressure, required
values.comment: The pressure that should be applied by a clamp.

values.label: Break
values.comment: The measured break.

values.label: Ascertained volume
values.comment: Endorsement of the true volume as ascertained or verified.

values.label: Unit weight
values.comment: The weight of a unit.

values.label: Total volume
values.comment: Total volume of goods and/or parcels.

values.label: Unit volume
values.comment: The volume of a unit.

values.label: Vertical center of gravity
values.comment: Distance of vertical center of gravity relative to item's base.

values.label: Maximum allowable transport stacking weight
values.comment: Maximum weight allowed to be stowed on top of an item during transport.

values.label: Carbon Dioxide
values.comment: Measurement of the carbon dioxide (C02) component.

values.label: Number of base units per pallet
values.comment: The number of base units contained on a pallet.

values.label: Colony forming unit
values.comment: Micro-organism colonies that are to be counted under determined conditions.

values.label: Diluted liquid volume
values.comment: The volume of liquid which results after a dilution agent has been added, e.g. undiluted orange juice of 200ml, after dilution with water the volume of diluted liquid equals 1 litre.

values.label: Energy efficiency
values.comment: A measurement of the energy efficiency of an article.

values.label: Number of layers
values.comment: Number of layers of a product or products within a package, container, etc.

values.label: Maximum demand
values.comment: The highest demand recorded during the period of recording of usage of the supply.

values.label: Number of pallet places
values.comment: The number of pallet places needed to store or to transport pallets (can be stacked).

values.label: Package net measurement, cubed
values.comment: An indication of the net cubed measurement of a package.

values.label: Power factor
values.comment: The ratio of the power dissipated (active power in kW) to the total power (which is the product of the input volts times amps given in kVa). When equipment which uses reactive power is being operated the power factor will be less than one.

values.label: Stacking factor excluding bottom item
values.comment: Maximum number of identical items stackable on top of item.

values.label: Breaking strength
values.comment: The measured breaking strength.

values.label: Breaking strength wet
values.comment: The measured breaking strength when wet.

values.label: Step size
values.comment: An indication of measurements in which options contained within a Customer Specific Article are available, e.g. 10 metre planks of wood may be sold in step sizes of 2 metres.

values.label: Number of units per package
values.comment: The number of identified units per package.

values.label: Number of units per layer
values.comment: Number of units of a product or package within one layer of a package, container, etc.

values.label: Weight per running metre
values.comment: A code used to indicate the weight per running metre of floor coverings over floor area.

values.label: Weight per square metre
values.comment: A code used to indicate the weight per square metre of floor coverings over floor area.

values.label: Acidity of meat
values.comment: The meat's acid quality or condition.

values.label: Slaughtering weight
values.comment: Weight immediately after slaughter.

values.label: Stacking factor including bottom item
values.comment: Maximum number of items stackable upon each other, including the bottom item.

values.label: Number of units in the width of a layer
values.comment: Number of units of a product or package which make up the width of a layer in a package, container, pallet, etc.

values.label: Number of units in the depth of a layer
values.comment: Number of units of a product or package which make up the depth of a layer in a package, container, pallet, etc.

values.label: Nestable percentage
values.comment: Extent expressed as a percentage to which an item can be nested within an identical item, e.g. paper cups.

values.label: Gross weight including carrier's equipment
values.comment: Weight (mass) of goods including packaging and the carrier's equipment. In this context 'carrier's equipment' means any material resources necessary to facilitate the transport and handling of the goods without having the ability to move by its own propulsion, e.g. pallet, container, etc.

values.label: Sugar content
values.comment: The rate of sugar.

values.label: Self-accelerating polymerization temperature (SAPT)
values.comment: The lowest temperature at which polymerization may occur for a substance as packed for transport.

values.label: Self-accelerating decomposition temperature (SADT)
values.comment: The lowest temperature at which self-accelerating decomposition may occur for a substance as packed for transport.

values.label: Control temperature
values.comment: The controlled transport temperature to avoid decomposition of self-reactive substances and organic peroxides.

values.label: Basis weight
values.comment: (6030) The measured basis weight.

values.label: Change
values.comment: The measured change.

values.label: Emergency temperature
values.comment: The temperature at which emergency response is required for self-reactive substances and organic peroxides.

values.label: Colour
values.comment: The measured colour.

values.label: Contents of package
values.comment: In combination with the other data elements of the actual segment this code indicates the measured content of a package.

values.label: Commercial weight
values.comment: Item weight considering its maximum possible humidity.

values.label: Core length
values.comment: To specify length of core on which product is to be placed.

values.label: Destination weight agreement

values.label: Diameter

values.label: Delta value L

values.comment: The measured density.

values.label: Depth

values.comment: The measured distance between points.

values.label: Estimated new weight

values.label: Elongation

values.label: Deficit weight

values.comment: The actual weight of the goods excluding packaging.

values.label: Outside diameter

values.label: Resistivity

values.label: Thickness

values.label: Time

values.comment: The weight per unit of length.
